dbd50c28-8747-4340-9260-ca5e92d924d5.4d764ffd-9618-4dc6-8498-6f43ef38854f.description=
Synopsis

 This flow\:
1. Finds Brocade sanSwitches in DEV,QA,PROD based on dataCenterSearch input (Dev only supports dataCenterSearch\="")
2. Flow then builds IP (and if inUK, builds domainId/FID corresponding list too)
3. Flow runs getAliasByPatternMatch in parallel (multi-instance), and builds success/fail list of IPs (update\: and now activeconfig/fabric info too)
4. Reports brocade/alias/wwpn if found, or error if cannot connect to IP, for each IP in OCI.

Inputs

    dataCenterSearch - report only IPs/domainIds matching the datacenter (requires ZZ preamble).  DEV only supports NULL, as OCI does not use domainId information.

    patternToMatch - grep alias to find on each sanSwitch

    searchDomainId - should we search each FID on brocade? (is inUK?)

Results

    flowStatus - Found alias/matchingWwpn on each Brocade if found, and any issue IPs if cant connect

Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
    Unknown - Some brocades couldnt connect and/or subflows failed.
   Failure - something went wront before getAliasesByPatternMatch

dbd50c28-8747-4340-9260-ca5e92d924d5.7341d0ee-155d-43fa-987b-fcfcf23f8d3f.description=

Synopsis\:
  This flow creates an alias for a WWN, with inputs for both in a paired list.  This can create multiple aliases in a single flow.

1) Check for Nulls, init vars
2) Connect to HPNA (JRAS or HPNA)
3) Output success/failure and new alias info.

"Mandatory" (checkForNull) Inputs\:
sanSwitch - IP of Brocade switch
alias_wwpn_pairedlist - alias1,wwpn1,alias2,wwpn2

Results\:
 flowOutput -new alias information, XML format.

Responses\:
failure - Either couldn't connect to device, or 1 or more commands failed against ${deviceIP}
success - Ran all commands successfully against ${deviceIP}
dbd50c28-8747-4340-9260-ca5e92d924d5.7a0b705e-9be9-4d05-95b6-9098258719b6.description=
Iterates through a list of values. If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list.

Inputs\:
separator - The list separator (or delimiter).
list - The list to be split

Responses\:
has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned.
failure - failed to process the list.
no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list.

Returns\:
The current element of the list, if the response is has more

dbd50c28-8747-4340-9260-ca5e92d924d5.description=
Summary
 - buildAlicreates will searchBrocadesByWWPN for each wwpn in $alicreateList, to determine which fabric to alicreate on.  Finally, will log into each fabric/IP and alicreate command for proper alias/wwpn paired_list.
 - based in input lists, will re-determine if ntap or cust, and append to Global variables created\: ${fabric}_ntap and ${fabric}_cust \= $aliasesNewlyCreated

Inputs
 - alicreateList\: output of both calls to aliasExistOrNeedChecker, provides list of WWPNs needed for alias creation.
 - fabricIPs\: list of 1 IP per fabric in this dataCenter
 - NTAPlifNameList\: provided from mandatory input of createAliasAndZoneByLists, corresponding to NTAPlifWwpnList of alias/wwpn assumed pairings.
 - NTAPlifWwpnList\: provided from mandatory input of createAliasAndZoneByLists, corresponding to NTAPlifNameList of alias/wwpn assumed pairings.
 - custHostnameList\: provided from mandatory input of createAliasAndZoneByLists, corresponding to custWwpnList of alias/wwpn assumed pairings.
 - custWwpnList\: provided from mandatory input of createAliasAndZoneByLists, corresponding to custHostnameList of alias/wwpn assumed pairings.

Outputs
 - Proper Aliases created on proper fabric
 - Appended output to Flow Output Variable $flowOutput, of alicreate XML output of createAliasRAS (x each fabric)
